channel.title: German worlds
channel.description:
Why don't bots work on german worlds? It couldn't be that hard to edit all that stuff, right? I'm sure if the bots where kept a closed community, then we wouldn't have to worry about them getting into the hands of rsbuddy or powerbot, either. I don't have any experience, but is anyone interested?
Srry fridder, I think if it's kept to a closed community we shouldn't have to worry. Plus, I would only mine in the mining guild, yews are the best profit for me atm.

item.title: German worlds
item.dc:creator: @T41 t4
item.description:
@T41 wrote:

[quote=“Fridder, post:35, topic:407778”][quote author=T4_ link=topic=509055.msg3698310#msg3698310 date=1312585094]

I would figure out how he did it, but I don’t trust RSBot anymore so I won’t download that.

Download the open-source shit, look through it a little bit, see what you can find and if it looks suspicious remove it. If you fuck up RSBot, redownload it.

Edit: I got it working, but none of the woodcutting scripts click the trees, or bank. They only walk. I changed it so instead of clicking when it says ‘chop’, I made it say what it says in German.

Actually, it’s a little strange. If you attempt to write the word in German or use something like entity.getActions()[0] (the first right click option), it won’t work. I’ll have to look more into how this works.
[/quote]

All right, let the community know if your onto something :[size=1pt][/size]D[/quote]
Publicly releasing it would defeat the entire purpose of botting on German worlds.

Read full topic
